org.apache.james.queue.activemq

Class ActiveMQMailQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.james.queue.jms.JMSMailQueue
      • org.apache.james.queue.activemq.ActiveMQMailQueue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ActiveMQSupport, MailPrioritySupport, MailQueue, ManageableMailQueue, JMSSupport

    public class ActiveMQMailQueue
extends JMSMailQueue
implements ActiveMQSupport

    MailQueue implementation which use an ActiveMQ Queue.

    This implementation require at ActiveMQ 5.4.0+.

    When a Mail attribute is found and is not one of the supported primitives, then the toString() method is called on the attribute value to convert it

    The implementation use BlobMessage or ObjectMessage, depending on the constructor which was used

    See http://activemq.apache .org/blob-messages.html for more details

    Some other supported feature is handling of priorities. See:
    http://activemq.apache.org/how-can-i-support-priority-queues.html

    For this just add a Mail attribute with name MailPrioritySupport.MAIL_PRIORITY to it. It should use one of the following value MailPrioritySupport.LOW_PRIORITY, MailPrioritySupport.NORMAL_PRIORITY, MailPrioritySupport.HIGH_PRIORITY

    To have a good throughput you should use a caching connection factory.
